FunctionObject.label: space_link_rx
FunctionObject.text: Provides a SOIS Packet Service interface to higher layers. Packet indications and requests are handled, and transferred over the simulated space link using the ZMQ messaging technology.

ProvidedInterfaceObject.label: pollSocket
ProvidedInterfaceObject.text: Polls a ZMQ socket for new packets.

CommentObject.comment: Adapt from service specific interfaces to a generic MAL interface. Inspects SDU type and Stage to determine which interface to call.
Decodes PUS packets, determines equivalent MO service request, and directs it to appropriate MO service provider via a service dispatcher.
Note that we only have one aggregation service provider in this deployment, so this dispatcher is present for illustration only
Allows run time selection of service provider. Effectively a cross bar switch. Determines correct provider by inspecting MAL URI
Handles setting of packet length in TM headers and CRC calculation and checking
Receives Space Packets from the space link. Maintains counters per APID
Dispatches Space Packets to MAL or PUS handling stacks according to APID.
Routes MAL messages according to service ID
Binding of MAL messages to Space Packets
